title.narrative: AG: Feed the Future Market Systems and Partnerships (MSP)

description.narrative: (USAID Bureau for Resilience and Food Security): Purpose: This activity will provide services and tools and facilitate evidence from researchers and practitioners to improve the effectiveness and impact of private sector engagement and market systems projects and activities on food security. This ensures that RFS' efforts to promote agriculture-led growth, enterprise-driven development, and the Journey to Self-Reliance are data-driven and informed by evidence and good practice...Activities: This activity will provide USAID Missions, USAID/Washington, and other US Government (USG) operating units and their implementing international and local partners with the knowledge, capacity, tools, technical assistance, and services required to design, implement, monitor, and evaluate private sector engagement and market systems development programs that build resilient communities and countries and lead to inclusive agriculture-led economic growth, improved food security and nutrition, and increased incomes for the poor. Illustrative activities could include market or value chain analysis, support for partnership development with local businesses around specific innovations, ex-post or impact studies on market systems interventions, and support for Mission peer-to-peer exchange. Actual activities will be demand-driven in collaboration with Mission buy-in..
